TopicDetails.title: Social Economy Missions

frameworkProgramme.description: Programme for the Competitiveness of Enterprises and small and medium-sized enterprises

TopicDetails.conditions:
1.   Eligible countries: described in section 5 of the Call document and in the eligible third countries list.


2.   Eligibility and admissibility conditions: described in sections 4 and 5 of the Call document.

     
      Proposal page limits and layout: Please refer to Part B of the standard proposal template.

3.   Evaluation

      3.1 Evaluation criteria, scoring and threshold: described in sections 7 and 8 of the Call document.
     
      3.2 For submission and evaluation process, see Guide for applicants.
   

4.   Indicative timetable for evaluation and grant agreement: described in section 2.6 of the Call document.
 

5.   Proposal templates and model grant agreements (MGA):

      Proposal templates are available in the submission system below.

       Multi-beneficiary Model Grant Agreement

Members of consortium are required to conclude a consortium agreement, in principle prior to the signature of the grant agreement.

6.   Additional documents:

  • COSME establishment act
  • COSME 2019 Work programme
  • COSME 2020 Work programme
TopicDetails.supportInfo:
F&T Portal FAQ – Submission of proposals.

IT Helpdesk – contact the IT helpdesk for questions such as forgotten passwords, access rights and roles, technical aspects of submission of proposals, etc.

H2020 Online Manual - Please use the manual with caution and only for the Participant Portal tools guidance, i.e. Submission service and Beneficiary register, because it is H2020 specific and does not cover the COSME rules. Some aspects of COSME are different to the provisions of the H2020 programmes.

Enterprise Europe Network – contact your EEN national contact for advice to businesses with special focus on SMEs. The support includes guidance on the EU research funding.

European IPR Helpdesk assists you on intellectual property issues.

Partner Search Services help you find a partner organisation for your proposal.

DG GROWTH website.
TopicDetails.sepTemplate:
To access the Electronic Submission Service, please click on the submission-button next to the type of action that corresponds to your proposal. You will then be asked to confirm your choice of the type of action and topic, as these cannot be changed in the submission system. Upon confirmation, you will be linked to the correct entry point.

To access existing draft proposals for this topic, please login to the Funding & Tenders Portal and select the My Proposals page of the My Area section.

callDetailsJSONItem.staticAdditionalInfo:
The total budget earmarked for the co-financing of projects is estimated at EUR 1 900 000.

The maximum grant per project will be EUR 100 000. The grant is limited to the maximum reimbursement rates as provided in section 11.2 - Funding forms of the Call for proposals.

EASME expects to fund 19 proposals. The funds will be allocated to the proposals with the best award criteria scores.
